var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"category":"section","location":"#ModelManager.jl","page":"Home","text":"Generic infrastructure for managing simulation-based modeling projects.\n\nModelManager.jl provides the base types, database management, variation handling, and runner infrastructure that simulator-specific packages (e.g., PhysiCellModelManager.jl) build on top of.","title":"ModelManager.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"#API-Reference","page":"Home","text":"","title":"API Reference"},{"category":"constant","location":"#ModelManager.mm_globals_ref","page":"Home","text":"mm_globals_ref\n\nModule-level Ref holding the active ModelManagerGlobals instance.\n\nSet by the concrete simulator package in its __init__, e.g.:\n\nfunction __init__()\n    ModelManager.mm_globals_ref[] = ModelManagerGlobals(simulator = MySimulator(), ...)\nend\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.mm_globals_ref"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.AbstractMonad","page":"Home","text":"AbstractMonad <: AbstractSampling\n\nAbstract type for Simulation and Monad.\n\nAll associated simulations share both input folders and variation IDs.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.AbstractMonad"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.AbstractSampling","page":"Home","text":"AbstractSampling <: AbstractTrial\n\nAbstract type for Simulation, Monad, and Sampling.\n\nAll associated simulations share the same input folders; only variations differ.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.AbstractSampling"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.AbstractSimulator","page":"Home","text":"AbstractSimulator\n\nAbstract supertype for simulator backends.\n\nConcrete subtypes are responsible for preparing and executing a single simulation via the runSimulation dispatch, and for providing simulator-specific metadata (version schema, display info, etc.).\n\nThis is the primary extension point for using the ModelManager infrastructure with any simulator. To support a new simulator:\n\nDefine MySimulator <: AbstractSimulator\nImplement the required interface methods listed below\n\nRequired interface methods\n\nrunSimulation(::MySimulator, simulation, monad_id; do_full_setup, force_recompile)\nsimulatorDir(::MySimulator)::String\nsimulatorVersionSchema(::MySimulator)::String\nsimulatorVersionIDName(::MySimulator)::String\nsimulatorVersionTableName(::MySimulator)::String\nresolveSimulatorVersionID(::MySimulator)::Int\ncurrentSimulatorVersionID(::MySimulator)::Int\nsimulatorInfo(::MySimulator)::String\npostInitDisplay(::MySimulator)\nsetupMonad(::MySimulator, monad; force_recompile::Bool)::Bool\nsetupSampling(::MySimulator, sampling; force_recompile::Bool)::Bool\naddVariationRows(::MySimulator, inputs, reference_variation_id, loc_dicts)::Vector{VariationID}\n\nNote: variationLocation is not part of the ModelManager interface.  The calling framework (e.g. PhysiCellModelManager) is responsible for resolving variation targets to their locations before constructing variation objects — the location::Symbol argument must be passed explicitly when constructing DiscreteVariation or DistributedVariation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.AbstractSimulator"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.AbstractTrial","page":"Home","text":"AbstractTrial\n\nAbstract type for the Simulation, Monad, Sampling, and Trial types.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.AbstractTrial"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.AbstractVariation","page":"Home","text":"AbstractVariation\n\nAbstract type for variations.\n\nSubtypes\n\nElementaryVariation, DiscreteVariation, DistributedVariation, CoVariation\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.AbstractVariation"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.AddVariationMethod","page":"Home","text":"AddVariationMethod\n\nAbstract type for variation sampling methods.\n\nSubtypes\n\nGridVariation, LHSVariation, SobolVariation, RBDVariation\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.AddVariationMethod"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.AddVariationsResult","page":"Home","text":"AddVariationsResult\n\nAbstract type for the result of addVariations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.AddVariationsResult"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.CoVariation","page":"Home","text":"CoVariation{T<:ElementaryVariation} <: AbstractVariation\n\nA co-variation of one or more ElementaryVariations that are varied together.\n\nEach constituent variation must be of the same subtype (all DiscreteVariation or all DistributedVariation).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.CoVariation"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.DiscreteVariation","page":"Home","text":"DiscreteVariation{T} <: ElementaryVariation\n\nThe location, target, and values of a discrete variation.\n\nFields\n\nlocation::Symbol: The location (input-folder category) for this variation.\ntarget::XMLPath: The XML path to the element being varied.\nvalues::Vector{T}: The possible values that the target can take on.\n\nA singleton value can be passed in place of values for convenience.\n\nlocation must be provided explicitly.  Simulator packages (e.g. PhysiCellModelManager) may provide convenience constructors that infer location from the target.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.DiscreteVariation"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.DistributedVariation","page":"Home","text":"DistributedVariation <: ElementaryVariation\n\nThe location, target, and distribution of a distributed variation.\n\nFields\n\nlocation::Symbol: The location (input-folder category) for this variation.\ntarget::XMLPath: The XML path to the element being varied.\ndistribution::Distribution: The distribution of the variation.\nflip::Bool=false: Whether to flip the distribution (iCDF of 1-x instead of x).\n\nlocation must be provided explicitly.  Simulator packages (e.g. PhysiCellModelManager) may provide convenience constructors that infer location from the target.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.DistributedVariation"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.ElementaryVariation","page":"Home","text":"ElementaryVariation <: AbstractVariation\n\nThe base type for variations of a single parameter.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.ElementaryVariation"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.GSAMethod","page":"Home","text":"GSAMethod\n\nAbstract type for global sensitivity analysis methods.\n\nSubtypes\n\nMOAT, Sobolʼ, RBD\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.GSAMethod"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.GSASampling","page":"Home","text":"GSASampling\n\nAbstract type for global sensitivity analysis sampling results.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.GSASampling"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.GridVariation","page":"Home","text":"GridVariation <: AddVariationMethod\n\nEnumerate all combinations of discrete variation values (full factorial grid).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.GridVariation"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.InputFolder","page":"Home","text":"InputFolder\n\nHold the information for a single input folder (location + folder name + metadata).\n\nCreated automatically by InputFolders constructors.\n\nFields\n\nlocation::Symbol: The location key (e.g. :config, :custom_code).\nid::Int: Database row ID for this folder.\nfolder::String: Folder name within data/inputs/<path_from_inputs>/.\nbasename::Union{String,Missing}: Primary input file name, or missing.\nrequired::Bool: Whether this location is required.\nvaried::Bool: Whether this folder supports parameter variations.\npath_from_inputs::String: Relative path from data/inputs/ to this folder.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.InputFolder"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.InputFolders","page":"Home","text":"InputFolders\n\nConsolidate the folder information for a simulation / monad / sampling.\n\nConstructors\n\nAll folders as keyword arguments (omitted ⟹ \"\"):\n\nInputFolders(; config=\"default\", custom_code=\"default\")\n\nRequired folders as positional args (alphabetical order), optional as kwargs:\n\nInputFolders(\"default\", \"default\"; ic_cell=\"cells_in_disc\")\n\nFields\n\ninput_folders::NamedTuple: Keys are location symbols; values are InputFolders.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.InputFolders"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.LHSVariation","page":"Home","text":"LHSVariation <: AddVariationMethod\n\nLatin Hypercube Sampling.\n\nFields\n\nn::Int: Number of samples.\nadd_noise::Bool=false: Whether to add noise within each bin.\nrng::AbstractRNG=Random.GLOBAL_RNG\northogonalize::Bool=true\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.LHSVariation"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.LatentVariation","page":"Home","text":"LatentVariation{T<:Union{Vector{<:Real},<:Distribution}} <: AbstractVariation\n\nA variation that uses latent parameters to generate target parameter values via mapping functions.\n\nWhereas CoVariations enforce a 1D relationship between parameters, LatentVariations allow multi-dimensional relationships via user-supplied maps. The latent parameters themselves are not stored in the database; only the derived target values are.\n\nInternally, ParsedVariations converts all variations to LatentVariations for processing.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.LatentVariation"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.MMOutput","page":"Home","text":"MMOutput{T<:AbstractTrial}\n\nHold the result of a run call.\n\nFields\n\ntrial::T: The trial that was run.\nn_scheduled::Int: Number of simulations scheduled in this run.\nn_success::Int: Number of simulations that completed successfully.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.MMOutput"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.MOAT","page":"Home","text":"MOAT <: GSAMethod\n\nMorris One-At-A-Time global sensitivity analysis.\n\nFields\n\nlhs_variation::LHSVariation\n\nExamples\n\nMOAT()      # default 15 base points\nMOAT(10)    # 10 base points\nMOAT(10; add_noise=true)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.MOAT"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.MOATSampling","page":"Home","text":"MOATSampling <: GSASampling\n\nResult of a MOAT sensitivity analysis.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.MOATSampling"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.ModelManagerGlobals","page":"Home","text":"ModelManagerGlobals\n\nMutable struct holding all global state for a ModelManager project.\n\nThe active instance is accessed via mm_globals.  Concrete simulator packages (e.g. PhysiCellModelManager) create an instance of this struct and register it via mm_globals_ref in their __init__.\n\nFields\n\ninitialized::Bool: true after initializeModelManager succeeds.\ndata_dir::String: Absolute path to the project data/ directory.\nsimulator::AbstractSimulator: The active simulator backend.\ninputs_dict::Dict{Symbol,Any}: Parsed contents of inputs.toml.\nproject_locations::ProjectLocations: Derived from inputs_dict.\ndb::SQLite.DB: Connection to the central project database.\nrun_on_hpc::Bool: true when sbatch is available (auto-detected).\nsbatch_options::Dict{String,Any}: Options forwarded to sbatch.\nmax_number_of_parallel_simulations::Int: Concurrency limit.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.ModelManagerGlobals"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.Monad","page":"Home","text":"Monad\n\nA group of identical-up-to-randomness simulations.\n\nConstructors\n\nMonad(inputs, variation_id; n_replicates=0, use_previous=true)\nMonad(monad_id; n_replicates=0, use_previous=true)\nMonad(simulation)\n\nFields\n\nid::Int\ninputs::InputFolders\nvariation_id::VariationID\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.Monad"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.ParsedVariations","page":"Home","text":"ParsedVariations{T<:LatentVariation}\n\nHolds all variations converted to LatentVariations, ready for sampling.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.ParsedVariations"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.ProjectLocations","page":"Home","text":"ProjectLocations\n\nA struct that contains information about the locations of input files in the project.\n\nCreated by reading the inputs.toml file in the data directory via parseProjectInputsConfigurationFile.\n\nFields\n\nall::NTuple{L,Symbol}: All registered location names (alphabetically sorted).\nrequired::NTuple{M,Symbol}: Locations whose input folder is mandatory.\nvaried::NTuple{N,Symbol}: Locations that support parameter variations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.ProjectLocations"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.RBD","page":"Home","text":"RBD <: GSAMethod\n\nRandom Balance Design global sensitivity analysis.\n\nFields\n\nrbd_variation::RBDVariation\nnum_harmonics::Int\n\nExamples\n\nRBD(15)\nRBD(15; num_harmonics=10)\nRBD(15; use_sobol=false)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.RBD"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.RBDSampling","page":"Home","text":"RBDSampling <: GSASampling\n\nResult of an RBD sensitivity analysis.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.RBDSampling"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.RBDVariation","page":"Home","text":"RBDVariation <: AddVariationMethod\n\nRandom Balance Design sampling.\n\nFields\n\nn::Int\nrng::AbstractRNG=Random.GLOBAL_RNG\nuse_sobol::Bool=true\npow2_diff::Union{Missing,Int}=missing\nnum_cycles::Union{Missing,Int,Rational}=missing\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.RBDVariation"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.Sampling","page":"Home","text":"Sampling\n\nA group of monads sharing the same input folders but differing in parameter values.\n\nFields\n\nid::Int\ninputs::InputFolders\nmonads::Vector{Monad}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.Sampling"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.Simulation","page":"Home","text":"Simulation\n\nA single run of the model.\n\nConstructors\n\nSimulation(simulation_id)          # retrieve existing\nSimulation(inputs, variation_id)   # create new (inserts into DB)\nSimulation(monad)                  # new sim with same params as monad\n\nFields\n\nid::Int\ninputs::InputFolders\nvariation_id::VariationID\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.Simulation"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.SimulationProcess","page":"Home","text":"SimulationProcess\n\nHolds the outcome of a single simulation run.\n\nFields\n\nsimulation::Simulation\nmonad_id::Int\nprocess::Union{Nothing,Base.Process}: nothing if the command could not be built.\nsuccess::Bool\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.SimulationProcess"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.SobolMM","page":"Home","text":"SobolMM\n\nASCII alias for Sobolʼ.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.SobolMM"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.SobolSampling","page":"Home","text":"SobolSampling <: GSASampling\n\nResult of a Sobolʼ sensitivity analysis.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.SobolSampling"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.SobolVariation","page":"Home","text":"SobolVariation <: AddVariationMethod\n\nSobol quasi-random sequence sampling.\n\nFields\n\nn::Int: Number of samples.\nn_matrices::Int=1: Number of design matrices.\nrandomization::RandomizationMethod=NoRand()\nskip_start::Union{Missing,Bool,Int}=missing\ninclude_one::Union{Missing,Bool}=missing\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.SobolVariation"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.Sobolʼ","page":"Home","text":"Sobolʼ <: GSAMethod\n\nSobol' variance-based global sensitivity analysis.\n\nThe ʼ (rasp) symbol avoids conflict with the Sobol module. Type \\rasp<tab> in VS Code. SobolMM is provided as a plain-ASCII alias.\n\nFields\n\nsobol_variation::SobolVariation\nsobol_index_methods::NamedTuple{(:first_order,:total_order),Tuple{Symbol,Symbol}}\n\nExamples\n\nSobolʼ(15)\nSobolʼ(15; sobol_index_methods=(first_order=:Jansen1999, total_order=:Jansen1999))\nSobolʼ(15; skip_start=true)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.Sobolʼ"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.Trial","page":"Home","text":"Trial\n\nA group of samplings that may have different input folders.\n\nFields\n\nid::Int\nsamplings::Vector{Sampling}\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.Trial"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.VariationID","page":"Home","text":"VariationID\n\nRecord the variation row IDs for each varied input location.\n\nA value of -1 means the location is not in use; 0 means the base (unvaried) file is being used.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.VariationID"},{"category":"type","location":"#ModelManager.XMLPath","page":"Home","text":"XMLPath\n\nHold an XML path as a vector of strings, where each element is a node in the path.\n\nA : in a path element denotes an attribute filter, e.g. \"cell_definition:name:default\" selects the <cell_definition> whose name attribute equals \"default\". A double-colon :: separates a parent tag from a child tag used as a filter.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.XMLPath"},{"category":"method","location":"#Base.run-Tuple{AbstractTrial}","page":"Home","text":"run(T::AbstractTrial; force_recompile, kwargs...)\n\nRun all pending simulations in T and return an MMOutput.\n\nkwargs are forwarded to postSimulationProcessing for each completed simulation.  For example, PhysiCellModelManager accepts prune_options.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.run"},{"category":"method","location":"#Base.run-Tuple{AddVariationMethod, Vararg{Any}}","page":"Home","text":"run([method=GridVariation()], inputs_or_ref, avs...; force_recompile=false, kwargs...)\n\nCreate a trial from inputs_or_ref and avs, then run it. kwargs are forwarded to run(::AbstractTrial; ...), which passes them to postSimulationProcessing.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.run"},{"category":"method","location":"#Base.run-Tuple{GSAMethod, InputFolders, AbstractVector{<:AbstractVariation}}","page":"Home","text":"run(method::GSAMethod, inputs::InputFolders, avs; functions, kwargs...)\nrun(method::GSAMethod, reference::AbstractMonad, avs; functions, kwargs...)\n\nRun a global sensitivity analysis and return a GSASampling result.\n\nkwargs are forwarded to run(::Sampling; ...) (e.g. force_recompile, simulator-specific options like prune_options).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Base.run"},{"category":"method","location":"#Distributions.cdf-Tuple{DiscreteVariation, Real}","page":"Home","text":"cdf(ev::ElementaryVariation, x::Real)\n\nGet the cumulative distribution function value of the variation at x.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Distributions.cdf"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.NormalDistributedVariation-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Symbol, XMLPath, T, T}} where T<:Real","page":"Home","text":"NormalDistributedVariation(location, target, mu, sigma; lb=-Inf, ub=Inf, flip=false)\n\nCreate a (possibly truncated) DistributedVariation with a Normal distribution.\n\nlocation must be provided explicitly.  Simulator packages (e.g. PhysiCellModelManager) may provide convenience constructors that infer location from the target.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.NormalDistributedVariation"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.UniformDistributedVariation-Union{Tuple{T}, Tuple{Symbol, XMLPath, T, T}} where T<:Real","page":"Home","text":"UniformDistributedVariation(location, xml_path, lb, ub; flip=false)\n\nCreate a DistributedVariation with a Uniform(lb, ub) distribution.\n\nlocation must be provided explicitly.  Simulator packages (e.g. PhysiCellModelManager) may provide convenience constructors that infer location from the target.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.UniformDistributedVariation"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager._createTrial-Tuple{AddVariationMethod, InputFolders, VariationID, Vector{<:AbstractVariation}, Integer, Bool}","page":"Home","text":"_createTrial(method, inputs, reference_variation_id, avs, n_replicates, use_previous)\n\nInternal implementation of createTrial.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager._createTrial"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.abstractSamplingForeignReferenceSubSchema-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"abstractSamplingForeignReferenceSubSchema()\n\nReturn the SQL fragment for foreign key constraints referencing the simulator version table and all input tables.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.abstractSamplingForeignReferenceSubSchema"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.addCDFVariations-Tuple{InputFolders, ParsedVariations, VariationID, AbstractMatrix{Float64}}","page":"Home","text":"addCDFVariations(inputs, pv, reference_variation_id, cdfs)\n\nConvert CDF samples to parameter values and write new variation rows to the database. Used internally by LHS, Sobol, and RBD addVariations implementations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.addCDFVariations"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.addFolderNameColumns!-Tuple{DataFrames.DataFrame}","page":"Home","text":"addFolderNameColumns!(df::DataFrame)\n\nAppend <location>_folder columns to df by looking up folder names.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.addFolderNameColumns!"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.addSimulationID-Tuple{Monad, Int64}","page":"Home","text":"addSimulationID(monad::Monad, simulation_id::Int)\n\nAppend simulation_id to monad's constituent IDs CSV (if not already present).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.addSimulationID"},{"category":"function","location":"#ModelManager.addVariationRows","page":"Home","text":"addVariationRows(sim::AbstractSimulator, inputs::InputFolders, reference_variation_id::VariationID, loc_dicts::Dict)\n\nWrite new variation rows to the simulator's per-location variation databases for inputs and return a Vector{VariationID} — one entry per column of values supplied in loc_dicts.\n\nloc_dicts maps each varied location Symbol to a tuple (values_matrix, types_vector, targets_vector) where values_matrix is n_targets × n_samples.\n\nCalled by addVariations (Grid, LHS, Sobol, RBD) after the generic sampling logic computes the CDF-derived parameter values.  Implementations are responsible for:\n\nEnsuring the required columns exist in the per-folder variation DB.\nInserting rows (or returning the existing ID when a row already exists).\nReturning one VariationID per sample point.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.addVariationRows"},{"category":"function","location":"#ModelManager.addVariations","page":"Home","text":"addVariations(method::AddVariationMethod, inputs::InputFolders, avs::Vector{<:AbstractVariation},\n              reference_variation_id::VariationID=VariationID(inputs))\n\nAdd variations to inputs using method and return an AddVariationsResult.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.addVariations"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.appendVariations-Tuple{Symbol, DataFrames.DataFrame}","page":"Home","text":"appendVariations(location::Symbol, df::DataFrame)\n\nJoin the varied parameters for location onto df.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.appendVariations"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.assertInitialized-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"assertInitialized()\n\nAssert that the model manager has been initialized, throwing an informative error if not.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.assertInitialized"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.buildWhereClause-Tuple{String, Vector{<:Integer}, Dict{<:AbstractString}}","page":"Home","text":"buildWhereClause(table_name::String, ids::Vector{<:Integer}, filters::Dict; db::SQLite.DB=centralDB())\n\nBuild a WHERE clause with ids and optional column filters.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.buildWhereClause"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.calculateGSA!-Tuple{GSASampling, AbstractVector{<:Function}}","page":"Home","text":"calculateGSA!(gsa_sampling, functions)\n\nCalculate sensitivity indices for each function in functions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.calculateGSA!"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.centralDB-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"centralDB()\n\nReturn the central SQLite.DB connection for the current project.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.centralDB"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.clearSimulatorArtifacts-Tuple{AbstractSimulator}","page":"Home","text":"clearSimulatorArtifacts(sim::AbstractSimulator)\n\nRemove all simulator-generated build artifacts from input folders during a database reset. The default implementation is a no-op.\n\nCalled by resetDatabase after all output folders have been deleted. Implementations should remove compiled executables, object files, and any other files generated by the simulator that do not belong to the base inputs.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.clearSimulatorArtifacts"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.collectSimulationTasks-Tuple{Simulation}","page":"Home","text":"collectSimulationTasks(T::AbstractTrial; force_recompile, do_full_setup)\n\nCollect Task objects for every simulation that needs to run under T.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.collectSimulationTasks"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.columnName-Tuple{Vector{<:AbstractString}}","page":"Home","text":"columnName(xml_path::Vector{<:AbstractString})\n\nJoin an XML path vector into a slash-separated column name string.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.columnName"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.columnsExist-Tuple{AbstractVector{<:AbstractString}, String}","page":"Home","text":"columnsExist(column_names, table_name::String; kwargs...)\ncolumnsExist(column_names, valid_column_names)\n\nReturn true if all column_names exist in the specified table (or list).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.columnsExist"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.compressIDs-Tuple{AbstractArray{Int64}}","page":"Home","text":"compressIDs(ids::AbstractArray{Int})\n\nCompress a sorted list of IDs into a compact run-length representation.\n\nConsecutive ranges are stored as \"first:last\" strings; isolated IDs are stored as plain integers.  This mirrors the on-disk format written by recordConstituentIDs.\n\nExamples\n\ncompressIDs([1, 2, 3, 5, 7, 8]) # → Tables.table([\"1:3\", \"5\", \"7:8\"])\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.compressIDs"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.constituentIDs-Tuple{String}","page":"Home","text":"constituentIDs(T::AbstractTrial)\nconstituentIDs(::Type{T}, id::Int)\n\nRead the constituent IDs for trial T from its CSV file.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.constituentIDs"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.constituentType-Tuple{Type{Simulation}}","page":"Home","text":"constituentType(T)\n\nReturn the type of the sub-objects of trial type T.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.constituentType"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.constituentTypeFilename-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","text":"constituentTypeFilename(T)\n\nReturn the CSV filename that stores the constituent IDs for type T.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.constituentTypeFilename"},{"category":"function","location":"#ModelManager.constructSelectQuery","page":"Home","text":"constructSelectQuery(table_name::String, condition_stmt::String=\"\"; selection::String=\"*\")\n\nBuild a SELECT SQL string for table_name.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.constructSelectQuery"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.continueMilestoneUpgrade-Tuple{VersionNumber, Bool}","page":"Home","text":"continueMilestoneUpgrade(version::VersionNumber, auto_upgrade::Bool)\n\nPrint a warning about the schema change at version and prompt the user to confirm unless auto_upgrade is true. Returns true if the upgrade should proceed, false if the user aborted.\n\nCall this at the top of any upgradeToMilestone implementation that makes large or destructive changes to the database schema.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.continueMilestoneUpgrade"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.createDefaultStatusCodesTable-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"createDefaultStatusCodesTable()\n\nCreate (if absent) and populate the status_codes table.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.createDefaultStatusCodesTable"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.createMMTable-Tuple{String, String}","page":"Home","text":"createMMTable(table_name::String, schema::String; db::SQLite.DB=centralDB())\n\nCreate a table in the central database if it does not already exist.\n\nThe table name must end in \"s\" (for ID naming conventions) and the schema must include a PRIMARY KEY column named <table_singular>_id.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.createMMTable"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.createSchema-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"createSchema()\n\nCreate all tables in the central database.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.createSchema"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.createSortedRBDMatrix-Tuple{Vector{VariationID}, Matrix{Int64}}","page":"Home","text":"createSortedRBDMatrix(variation_ids, rbd_sorting_inds)\n\nSort variation IDs according to the RBD parameter ordering.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.createSortedRBDMatrix"},{"category":"function","location":"#ModelManager.createTrial","page":"Home","text":"createTrial([method=GridVariation()], inputs::InputFolders, avs::Vector{<:AbstractVariation}=AbstractVariation[];\n            n_replicates::Integer=1, use_previous::Bool=true)\n\nReturn an AbstractTrial (Simulation, Monad, or Sampling) from the given inputs and variations.\n\nThe method controls how the variation space is sampled (default: GridVariation()). Other options: LHSVariation, SobolVariation, RBDVariation.\n\nAlternate forms (all accept an optional leading method argument)\n\ncreateTrial(inputs, av::AbstractVariation; ...)            # single variation\ncreateTrial(reference::AbstractMonad, avs; ...)            # start from a reference monad\ncreateTrial(output_ref::MMOutput{<:AbstractMonad}, avs; ...)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.createTrial"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.currentSimulatorVersionID-Tuple{AbstractSimulator}","page":"Home","text":"currentSimulatorVersionID(sim::AbstractSimulator)::Int\n\nReturn the integer row ID of the currently active simulator version.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.currentSimulatorVersionID"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.currentSimulatorVersionID-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"currentSimulatorVersionID()\n\nReturn the current simulator version row ID from the database. Delegates to currentSimulatorVersionID(sim) on the active simulator.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.currentSimulatorVersionID"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.dataDir-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"dataDir()\n\nReturn the path to the current project's data/ directory.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.dataDir"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.databaseDiagnostics-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"databaseDiagnostics()\n\nCheck consistency between the database and the output folders. Prints warnings for any discrepancies found.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.databaseDiagnostics"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.dbVersionTableName-Tuple{AbstractSimulator}","page":"Home","text":"dbVersionTableName(sim::AbstractSimulator)::String\n\nReturn the name of the SQLite table used to persist the package version in the project database (e.g. \"pcmm_version\"). The generic upgrade machinery reads and writes this table to track which version a given database was last migrated to.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.dbVersionTableName"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.defaultJobOptions-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"defaultJobOptions()\n\nReturn a Dict with default SLURM options.\n\nCurrent defaults:\n\n\"job-name\" — simulation_id -> \"S$(simulation_id)\"\n\"mem\" — \"1G\"\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.defaultJobOptions"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.defaultLatentParameterNames-Tuple{Vector, Vector{XMLPath}}","page":"Home","text":"defaultLatentParameterNames(latent_parameters::Vector, targets::Vector{XMLPath})\n\nGenerate default names for latent parameters based on target column names.\n\nFor each latent parameter, the name is constructed as: \"<target_1> | <target_2> | ... | lp#<i>\" where <target_n> is the column name of the n-th target parameter and <i> is the index of the latent parameter.\n\nReturns\n\nVector{String}: A vector of default names for the latent parameters.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.defaultLatentParameterNames"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.deleteAllSimulations-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"deleteAllSimulations(; kwargs...)\n\nDelete all simulations. See deleteSimulations for keyword arguments.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.deleteAllSimulations"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.deleteMonad-Tuple{AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"Home","text":"deleteMonad(monad_ids; delete_subs, delete_supers)\n\nDelete monads by ID, optionally cascading to their simulations and to empty samplings/trials above them.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.deleteMonad"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.deleteSampling-Tuple{AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"Home","text":"deleteSampling(sampling_ids; delete_subs, delete_supers)\n\nDelete samplings by ID, optionally cascading.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.deleteSampling"},{"category":"function","location":"#ModelManager.deleteSimulation","page":"Home","text":"deleteSimulation(args...; kwargs...)\n\nAlias for deleteSimulations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.deleteSimulation"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.deleteSimulations-Tuple{AbstractVector{<:Union{Missing, Integer}}}","page":"Home","text":"deleteSimulations(simulation_ids; delete_supers, filters)\ndeleteSimulation(args...; kwargs...)\n\nDelete simulations from the database and from disk.\n\nIf delete_supers is true (default), also removes any monads/samplings/trials that become empty after the deletion.  filters adds extra SQL WHERE conditions.\n\nExamples\n\ndeleteSimulations(1:3)\ndeleteSimulations(4)\ndeleteSimulations(1:100; filters=Dict(\"config_id\" => 1))\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.deleteSimulations"},{"category":"function","location":"#ModelManager.deleteSimulationsByStatus","page":"Home","text":"deleteSimulationsByStatus(status_codes_to_delete::Vector{String}=[\"Failed\"]; user_check::Bool=true)\ndeleteSimulationsByStatus(status_code_to_delete::String; user_check::Bool=true)\n\nDelete simulations filtered by status code.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.deleteSimulationsByStatus"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.deleteTrial-Tuple{AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"Home","text":"deleteTrial(trial_ids; delete_subs)\n\nDelete trials by ID, optionally cascading to their samplings.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.deleteTrial"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.dispatchSimulation-Tuple{Simulation}","page":"Home","text":"dispatchSimulation(simulation; monad_id, do_full_setup, force_recompile)\n\nDispatch a single simulation via runSimulation on the active simulator.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.dispatchSimulation"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.eraseSimulationIDFromConstituents-Tuple{Int64}","page":"Home","text":"eraseSimulationIDFromConstituents(simulation_id::Int; monad_id)\n\nRemove simulation_id from its monad's constituent CSV.  If the monad becomes empty, the monad (and its superiors) are deleted.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.eraseSimulationIDFromConstituents"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.evaluateFunctionOnSampling-Tuple{GSASampling, Function}","page":"Home","text":"evaluateFunctionOnSampling(gsa_sampling, f)\n\nEvaluate f (a function of simulation_id) on each monad in the sampling, averaging replicates.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.evaluateFunctionOnSampling"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.folderIsVaried-Tuple{Symbol, String}","page":"Home","text":"folderIsVaried(location::Symbol, folder::String)\n\nReturn true if folder in location can have parameter variations applied.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.folderIsVaried"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.generateLHSCDFs-Tuple{Int64, Int64}","page":"Home","text":"generateLHSCDFs(n::Int, d::Int; add_noise=false, rng=Random.GLOBAL_RNG, orthogonalize=true)\n\nGenerate a Latin Hypercube Sample of CDFs for n samples in d dimensions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.generateLHSCDFs"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.generateRBDCDFs-Tuple{RBDVariation, Int64}","page":"Home","text":"generateRBDCDFs(rbd_variation::RBDVariation, d::Int)\n\nGenerate CDFs and sorting indices for a Random Balance Design in d dimensions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.generateRBDCDFs"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.generateSobolCDFs-Tuple{Int64, Int64}","page":"Home","text":"generateSobolCDFs(n::Int, d::Int[; n_matrices::Int=1, randomization::RandomizationMethod=NoRand(), skip_start::Union{Missing, Bool, Int}=missing, include_one::Union{Missing, Bool}=missing])\n\nGenerate n_matrices Sobol sequences of the Cumulative Distribution Functions (CDFs) for n samples in d dimensions.\n\nThe subsequence of the Sobol sequence is chosen based on the value of n and the value of include_one. If it is one less than a power of 2, e.g. n=7, skip 0 and start from 0.5. Otherwise, it will always start from 0. If it is one more than a power of 2, e.g. n=9, include 1 (unless include_one is false).\n\nThe skip_start field can be used to control this by skipping the start of the sequence. If skip_start is true, skip to the smallest consecutive subsequence with the same denominator that has at least n elements. If skip_start is false, start from 0. If skip_start is an integer, skip that many elements in the sequence, e.g. skip_start=1 skips 0 and starts at 0.5.\n\nIf you want to include 1 in the sequence, set include_one to true. If you want to exclude 1 (in the case of n=9, e.g.), set include_one to false.\n\nArguments\n\nn::Int: The number of samples to take.\nd::Int: The number of dimensions to sample.\nn_matrices::Int=1: The number of matrices to use in the Sobol sequence (effectively, the dimension of the sample is d x n_matrices).\nrandomization::RandomizationMethod=NoRand(): The randomization method to use on the deterministic Sobol sequence.\nskip_start::Union{Missing, Bool, Int}=missing: Whether to skip the start of the sequence. missing means ModelManager will choose the best option.\ninclude_one::Union{Missing, Bool}=missing: Whether to include 1 in the sequence. missing means ModelManager will choose the best option.\n\nReturns\n\ncdfs::Array{Float64, 3}: The CDFs for the samples. First dimension is features, second is matrix index, third is sample points.\n\nExamples\n\ncdfs = ModelManager.generateSobolCDFs(11, 3)\nsize(cdfs)\n# output\n(3, 1, 11)\n\ncdfs = ModelManager.generateSobolCDFs(7, 5; n_matrices=2)\nsize(cdfs)\n# output\n(5, 2, 7)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.generateSobolCDFs"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.getDBPackageVersion-Tuple{AbstractSimulator, SQLite.DB}","page":"Home","text":"getDBPackageVersion(sim::AbstractSimulator, db::SQLite.DB)::VersionNumber\n\nReturn the package version recorded in db under dbVersionTableName(sim).\n\nIf the table does not yet exist it is created and stamped with the current getPackageVersion — this handles fresh databases that pre-date the versioning system.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.getDBPackageVersion"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.getInputFolderDescription-Tuple{AbstractSimulator, String}","page":"Home","text":"getInputFolderDescription(sim::AbstractSimulator, path_to_folder::String)::String\n\nReturn a human-readable description for the input folder at path_to_folder.\n\nCalled by insertFolder when inserting a new folder into the database. The default implementation returns \"\".  Simulator packages may override this to read metadata from a file in the folder (e.g. a metadata.xml or TOML file).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.getInputFolderDescription"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.getMonadIDDataFrame-Tuple{GSASampling}","page":"Home","text":"getMonadIDDataFrame(gsa_sampling::GSASampling)\n\nReturn the DataFrame of monad IDs that define the sampling scheme.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.getMonadIDDataFrame"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.getPackageVersion-Tuple{AbstractSimulator}","page":"Home","text":"getPackageVersion(sim::AbstractSimulator)::VersionNumber\n\nReturn the runtime version of the package that owns sim by querying Pkg.\n\nIf the current project IS that package (i.e. running tests from within the package itself), Pkg.project().version is returned directly. Otherwise, the loaded dependency list is searched by packageName.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.getPackageVersion"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.initializeDatabase-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"initializeDatabase()\n\nInitialize the central database, creating the schema if it does not already exist.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.initializeDatabase"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.initializeInputFolder-Tuple{AbstractSimulator, Any}","page":"Home","text":"initializeInputFolder(sim::AbstractSimulator, input_folder)\n\nPerform any simulator-specific initialization for a newly-inserted input folder.\n\nCalled by insertFolder after the folder row has been written to the database and the per-folder variations SQLite database has been created. The default implementation is a no-op.\n\nImplementations may, for example, compile an initial XML parameter file from a template, create derived assets, etc.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.initializeInputFolder"},{"category":"function","location":"#ModelManager.initializeModelManager","page":"Home","text":"initializeModelManager(simulator::AbstractSimulator, data_dir::String; kwargs...)\n\nInitialize ModelManager for a project rooted at data_dir using simulator as the concrete backend.\n\nThis is the generic entry point that simulator packages (e.g. PhysiCellModelManager) should call from their own initialization logic after constructing their AbstractSimulator instance.  A complete implementation is expected to:\n\nConstruct a ModelManagerGlobals with the provided simulator and data_dir and assign it to mm_globals_ref[].\nConnect to (or create) the central project database.\nCall postInitDisplay to print startup information.\n\nThis stub must be extended (or wrapped) by the simulator package.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.initializeModelManager"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.inputFolderID-Tuple{Symbol, String}","page":"Home","text":"inputFolderID(location::Symbol, folder::String)\n\nReturn the database row ID for folder in location.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.inputFolderID"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.inputFolderName-Tuple{Symbol, Int64}","page":"Home","text":"inputFolderName(location::Symbol, id::Int)\n\nReturn the folder name for the database row with id in location.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.inputFolderName"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.inputIDsSubSchema-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"inputIDsSubSchema()\n\nReturn the SQL fragment for all input ID columns.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.inputIDsSubSchema"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.inputVariationIDsSubSchema-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"inputVariationIDsSubSchema()\n\nReturn the SQL fragment for all variation ID columns.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.inputVariationIDsSubSchema"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.inputsDict-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"inputsDict()\n\nReturn the parsed inputs.toml dictionary for the current project.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.inputsDict"},{"category":"function","location":"#ModelManager.insertFolder","page":"Home","text":"insertFolder(location::Symbol, folder::String, description::String=\"\")\n\nInsert folder into the database for location (if not already present), create its per-folder variations SQLite database, and call initializeInputFolder on the active simulator.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.insertFolder"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.isInitialized-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"isInitialized()\n\nReturn true if the model manager has been successfully initialized.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.isInitialized"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.isRunningOnHPC-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"isRunningOnHPC()\n\nReturn true if the current environment is an HPC environment, false otherwise.\n\nCurrently checks for a SLURM environment by probing for the sbatch command.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.isRunningOnHPC"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.isStarted-Tuple{Int64}","page":"Home","text":"isStarted(simulation_id::Int[; new_status_code])\n\nReturn true if the simulation has been started.  Optionally update its status atomically (using an EXCLUSIVE transaction when a new status is provided).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.isStarted"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationFolder-Tuple{Union{String, Symbol}}","page":"Home","text":"locationFolder(location::Union{String,Symbol})\n\nReturn the name of the folder for location within data/inputs/. Defaults to locationTableName.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationFolder"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationIDName-Tuple{Union{String, Symbol}}","page":"Home","text":"locationIDName(location)\n\nReturn the ID column name for location (e.g. \"config_id\").\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationIDName"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationIDNames-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"locationIDNames()\n\nReturn an iterator over the ID column names for all locations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationIDNames"},{"category":"function","location":"#ModelManager.locationPath","page":"Home","text":"locationPath(location::Symbol[, folder])\n\nReturn the path to location's input directory.  If folder is given, join it.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationPath"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationPath-Tuple{InputFolder}","page":"Home","text":"locationPath(input_folder::InputFolder)\n\nReturn the full path to the input folder described by input_folder.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationPath"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationPath-Tuple{Symbol, AbstractSampling}","page":"Home","text":"locationPath(location::Symbol, S::AbstractSampling)\n\nReturn the full path to the input folder for location used by sampling S.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationPath"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationTableName-Tuple{Union{String, Symbol}}","page":"Home","text":"locationTableName(location)\n\nReturn the database table name for location (e.g. \"configs\").\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationTableName"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationVariationIDName-Tuple{Union{String, Symbol}}","page":"Home","text":"locationVariationIDName(location)\n\nReturn the variation ID column name for location (e.g. \"config_variation_id\").\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationVariationIDName"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationVariationIDNames-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"locationVariationIDNames()\n\nReturn an iterator over the variation ID column names for all varied locations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationVariationIDNames"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationVariationsDBName-Tuple{Union{String, Symbol}}","page":"Home","text":"locationVariationsDBName(location::Union{String,Symbol})\n\nReturn the filename of the per-folder variations SQLite database for location.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationVariationsDBName"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationVariationsDatabase-Tuple{Symbol, String}","page":"Home","text":"locationVariationsDatabase(location::Symbol, folder::String)\n\nReturn a SQLite.DB connection to the per-folder variations database for location/folder, nothing if the folder is empty (location unused), or missing if the variations DB file does not exist.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationVariationsDatabase"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationVariationsFolder-Tuple{Union{String, Symbol}}","page":"Home","text":"locationVariationsFolder(location)\n\nReturn the name of the variations folder for location.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationVariationsFolder"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationVariationsTable-Tuple{String, SQLite.DB}","page":"Home","text":"locationVariationsTable(query::String, db::SQLite.DB; remove_constants::Bool=false)\n\nReturn a DataFrame from query against db, dropping the par_key column. Removes constant columns if remove_constants is true and there is more than one row.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationVariationsTable"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationVariationsTable-Tuple{Symbol, AbstractSampling}","page":"Home","text":"locationVariationsTable(location::Symbol, S::AbstractSampling; remove_constants::Bool=false)\n\nReturn a DataFrame of variation rows for the given location and sampling.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationVariationsTable"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationVariationsTable-Tuple{Symbol, Missing, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"Home","text":"locationVariationsTable(location::Symbol, ::Missing, variation_ids; kwargs...)\n\nReturn a single-column DataFrame for a location whose folder has no variations database (all IDs = 0).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationVariationsTable"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationVariationsTable-Tuple{Symbol, Nothing, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"Home","text":"locationVariationsTable(location::Symbol, ::Nothing, variation_ids; kwargs...)\n\nReturn a single-column DataFrame for a location that is not being used (all IDs = -1).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationVariationsTable"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationVariationsTable-Tuple{Symbol, SQLite.DB, AbstractVector{<:Integer}}","page":"Home","text":"locationVariationsTable(location::Symbol, variations_database::SQLite.DB, variation_ids::AbstractVector{<:Integer}; remove_constants::Bool=false)\n\nReturn a DataFrame of variation rows for variation_ids from variations_database.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationVariationsTable"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.locationVariationsTableName-Tuple{Union{String, Symbol}}","page":"Home","text":"locationVariationsTableName(location)\n\nReturn the name of the variations table for location (e.g. \"config_variations\").\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.locationVariationsTableName"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.lowerClassString-Union{Tuple{Type{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T<:AbstractTrial","page":"Home","text":"lowerClassString(T)\n\nReturn the lowercase name of T's concrete type (e.g. \"simulation\").\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.lowerClassString"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.methodString-Tuple{GSASampling}","page":"Home","text":"methodString(gsa_sampling::GSASampling)\n\nReturn a lowercase string identifier for the GSA method (e.g. \"moat\", \"sobol\").\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.methodString"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.mm_globals-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"mm_globals()::ModelManagerGlobals\n\nReturn the active ModelManagerGlobals instance.\n\nThrows an assertion error if no simulator package has registered its globals yet.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.mm_globals"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.monadIDs-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"monadIDs()\n\nReturn all monad IDs in the database.  Overloaded forms accept a monad, sampling, or trial object.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.monadIDs"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.monadsSchema-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"monadsSchema()\n\nReturn the SQL schema string for the monads table.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.monadsSchema"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.necessaryInputsPresent-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"necessaryInputsPresent()\n\nReturn true if all required input directories exist.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.necessaryInputsPresent"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.orthogonalLHS-Tuple{Int64, Int64}","page":"Home","text":"orthogonalLHS(k::Int, d::Int)\n\nGenerate an orthogonal Latin Hypercube Sample in d dimensions with k subdivisions.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.orthogonalLHS"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.packageName-Tuple{AbstractSimulator}","page":"Home","text":"packageName(sim::AbstractSimulator)::String\n\nReturn the registered Julia package name for this simulator framework (e.g. \"PhysiCellModelManager\"). Used by getPackageVersion to look up the runtime version via Pkg.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.packageName"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.parseProjectInputsConfigurationFile-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"parseProjectInputsConfigurationFile()\n\nParse inputs.toml and update mm_globals with the resulting ProjectLocations and inputs_dict.\n\nReturns true on success, false if the file is missing or malformed.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.parseProjectInputsConfigurationFile"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.pathToInputsConfig-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"pathToInputsConfig()\n\nReturn the path to inputs.toml.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.pathToInputsConfig"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.pathToOutputFolder-Tuple{Int64}","page":"Home","text":"pathToOutputFolder(simulation_id::Int)\n\nReturn the path to the output folder for simulation_id.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.pathToOutputFolder"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.perturbVariation-Tuple{ParsedVariations, InputFolders, VariationID, AbstractVector{<:Real}}","page":"Home","text":"perturbVariation(pv, inputs, reference_variation_id, cdf_col)\n\nGenerate one-at-a-time perturbations of cdf_col for MOAT analysis.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.perturbVariation"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.populateTableOnFeatureSubset-Tuple{SQLite.DB, String, String}","page":"Home","text":"populateTableOnFeatureSubset(db::SQLite.DB, source_table::String, target_table::String; column_mapping::Dict{String,String}=Dict{String,String}())\n\nPopulate a target_table with rows from source_table. Columns in source_table that exist (possibly under a different name) in target_table are copied; extras are ignored. Use column_mapping to rename columns during the copy (source_name => target_name).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.populateTableOnFeatureSubset"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.postInitDisplay-Tuple{AbstractSimulator}","page":"Home","text":"postInitDisplay(sim::AbstractSimulator)\n\nPrint simulator-specific information after initialization.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.postInitDisplay"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.postSimulationProcessing-Tuple{AbstractSimulator, Any}","page":"Home","text":"postSimulationProcessing(sim::AbstractSimulator, simulation_process; kwargs...)\n\nPerform any simulator-specific work immediately after a simulation finishes.\n\nCalled by processSimulationTask for every completed simulation. The default implementation is a no-op; simulator packages override this to clean up error files, prune output, log diagnostics, etc.\n\nCommon keyword arguments (simulator-defined):\n\nprune_options — options controlling which output files to delete (used by PhysiCellModelManager).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.postSimulationProcessing"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.prepCmdForWrap-Tuple{Cmd}","page":"Home","text":"prepCmdForWrap(cmd::Cmd)\n\nStrip surrounding backticks from the string representation of cmd.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.prepCmdForWrap"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.prepareHPCCommand-Tuple{Cmd, Int64}","page":"Home","text":"prepareHPCCommand(cmd::Cmd, simulation_id::Int)\n\nWrap cmd in an sbatch invocation using the global job options.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.prepareHPCCommand"},{"category":"function","location":"#ModelManager.printInputFolders","page":"Home","text":"printInputFolders(io::IO, input_folders::InputFolders, n_indent::Int=0)\n\nPrint the folder information for each used location in input_folders.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.printInputFolders"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.printSimulationsTable-Tuple","page":"Home","text":"printSimulationsTable(args...; sink=println, kwargs...)\n\nPrint a table of simulations and their varied values. See simulationsTable.\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\nsink: A function to receive the DataFrame (default println). Can also use CSV.write.\n\nExamples\n\nprintSimulationsTable([simulation_1, monad_3, sampling_2, trial_1])\n\nsim_ids = [1, 2, 3]\nprintSimulationsTable(sim_ids; remove_constants=false)\n\nusing CSV\nprintSimulationsTable(; sink=CSV.write(\"temp.csv\"))\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.printSimulationsTable"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.processSimulationTask-Tuple{Any}","page":"Home","text":"processSimulationTask(simulation_task; kwargs...)\n\nSchedule and fetch a simulation task, then call postSimulationProcessing on the active simulator.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.processSimulationTask"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.projectLocations-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"projectLocations()\n\nReturn the ProjectLocations for the current project.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.projectLocations"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.queryToDataFrame-Tuple{String}","page":"Home","text":"queryToDataFrame(query::String; db::SQLite.DB=centralDB(), is_row::Bool=false)\n\nExecute query and return the result as a DataFrame.\n\nIf is_row is true, asserts that exactly one row is returned.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.queryToDataFrame"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.quietRun-Tuple{Cmd}","page":"Home","text":"quietRun(cmd::Cmd)\n\nRun the command with stdout and stderr redirected to devnull so no output goes to the console.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.quietRun"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.recognizedStatusCodes-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"recognizedStatusCodes()\n\nReturn the list of valid simulation status code strings.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.recognizedStatusCodes"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.recordConstituentIDs-Tuple{Type{<:AbstractTrial}, Int64, Array{Int64}}","page":"Home","text":"recordConstituentIDs(T::Type{<:AbstractTrial}, id::Int, ids::Array{Int})\nrecordConstituentIDs(T::AbstractTrial, ids::Array{Int})\n\nWrite the constituent IDs of an AbstractTrial to a CSV file inside its output folder.  The file is named after the constituent type (e.g. simulations.csv inside a monad folder).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.recordConstituentIDs"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.recordSensitivityScheme-Tuple{GSASampling}","page":"Home","text":"recordSensitivityScheme(gsa_sampling)\n\nWrite the monad ID scheme to a CSV file inside the sampling's trial folder.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.recordSensitivityScheme"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.reinitializeDatabase-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"reinitializeDatabase()\n\nReinitialize the database, scanning data/inputs/ to register any new folders.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.reinitializeDatabase"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.resetDatabase-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"resetDatabase(; force_reset, force_continue)\n\nReset the database after user confirmation: delete all output folders, clear all variation files, call clearSimulatorArtifacts on the active simulator, then reinitialize the database.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.resetDatabase"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.resetFolder-Tuple{Symbol, String}","page":"Home","text":"resetFolder(location::Symbol, folder::String)\n\nRemove the variations DB and variations folder from folder in location.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.resetFolder"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.resolvePackageVersion-Tuple{AbstractSimulator, SQLite.DB}","page":"Home","text":"resolvePackageVersion(sim::AbstractSimulator, db::SQLite.DB; auto_upgrade::Bool=false)::Bool\n\nCompare the runtime package version with the version recorded in db and upgrade if needed.\n\nIf the database is newer than the package, prints an error and returns false (the user must upgrade their package).\nIf versions match, returns true immediately.\nIf the package is newer, calls upgradePackage and returns its result.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.resolvePackageVersion"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.resolveSimulatorVersionID-Tuple{AbstractSimulator}","page":"Home","text":"resolveSimulatorVersionID(sim::AbstractSimulator)::Int\n\nResolve the current simulator version against the database, inserting a new row if necessary. Returns the resolved integer version ID.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.resolveSimulatorVersionID"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.rm_hpc_safe-Tuple{String}","page":"Home","text":"rm_hpc_safe(path::String; force, recursive)\n\nRemove path, using a .trash/ staging area on HPC (NFS) filesystems to avoid lock issues.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.rm_hpc_safe"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.runAbstractTrial-Tuple{AbstractTrial}","page":"Home","text":"runAbstractTrial(T::AbstractTrial; kwargs...)\n\nDeprecated alias for run.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.runAbstractTrial"},{"category":"function","location":"#ModelManager.runSensitivitySampling","page":"Home","text":"runSensitivitySampling(method, inputs, pv; kwargs...)\n\nInternal dispatch: create the sampling design, run simulations, and return a GSASampling. kwargs are forwarded to run(::Sampling; ...).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.runSensitivitySampling"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.runSimulation-Tuple{AbstractSimulator, Vararg{Any}}","page":"Home","text":"runSimulation(sim::AbstractSimulator, simulation, monad_id::Int; do_full_setup::Bool=true, force_recompile::Bool=false)\n\nPrepare inputs for and execute a single simulation using the given simulator backend.\n\nImplementations are responsible for:\n\nPreparing any varied input files for this simulation.\nCompiling / loading custom code (if applicable) when do_full_setup is true.\nExecuting the simulation (e.g. launching a subprocess, calling a Julia function).\nUpdating the database with the success status.\n\nReturn a SimulationProcess describing the outcome.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.runSimulation"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.samplingsSchema-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"samplingsSchema()\n\nReturn the SQL schema string for the samplings table.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.samplingsSchema"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.sanitizePathElement-Tuple{String}","page":"Home","text":"sanitizePathElement(path_element::String)\n\nValidate and return path_element, raising an ArgumentError for unsafe values.\n\nDisallows \"..\", absolute paths, and characters in ~*?<>|:.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.sanitizePathElement"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.sensitivityResults!-Tuple{GSASampling, AbstractVector{<:Function}}","page":"Home","text":"sensitivityResults!(gsa_sampling, functions)\n\nCalculate sensitivity indices for functions and record the sampling scheme.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.sensitivityResults!"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.setJobOptions-Tuple{Dict}","page":"Home","text":"setJobOptions(options::Dict)\n\nMerge options into the global sbatch_options dictionary.\n\nEach key–value pair becomes a --key=value flag appended to the sbatch command when running simulations on an HPC. Values that are Functions are called with the simulation ID at runtime.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.setJobOptions"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.setNumberOfParallelSims-Tuple{Int64}","page":"Home","text":"setNumberOfParallelSims(n::Int)\n\nSet the maximum number of parallel simulations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.setNumberOfParallelSims"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.setupMonad-Tuple{AbstractSimulator, Vararg{Any}}","page":"Home","text":"setupMonad(sim::AbstractSimulator, monad; force_recompile::Bool=false)::Bool\n\nPerform all monad-level setup (compilation, input folder preparation) before launching per-simulation tasks. Return true on success, false on failure.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.setupMonad"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.setupSampling-Tuple{AbstractSimulator, Vararg{Any}}","page":"Home","text":"setupSampling(sim::AbstractSimulator, sampling; force_recompile::Bool=false)::Bool\n\nPerform all sampling-level setup (typically: compile the shared custom code once) before collecting monad tasks. Return true on success, false on failure.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.setupSampling"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.shellCommandExists-Tuple{Union{Cmd, String}}","page":"Home","text":"shellCommandExists(cmd::Union{String,Cmd})\n\nCheck if a shell command exists in the current environment.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.shellCommandExists"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.shortLocationVariationID-Tuple{Symbol}","page":"Home","text":"shortLocationVariationID(fieldname::Symbol)\nshortLocationVariationID(fieldname::String)\nshortLocationVariationID(type::Type, fieldname)\n\nReturn the abbreviated column-name symbol for fieldname's variation ID in display tables.\n\nDispatches to shortLocationVariationID(simulator(), fieldname). The default implementation returns locationVariationIDName(fieldname) |> Symbol. Simulator packages should extend shortLocationVariationID(::TheirSimulator, fieldname::Symbol) to provide custom abbreviations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.shortLocationVariationID"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.shortVariationName-Tuple{Symbol, String}","page":"Home","text":"shortVariationName(location::Symbol, name::String)\n\nReturn the display name for variation column name at location.\n\nDispatches to shortVariationName(simulator(), location, name). The default returns name unchanged. Simulator packages should extend shortVariationName(::TheirSimulator, location, name) to provide human-readable column names.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.shortVariationName"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.simulationFailed-Tuple{Simulation, Int64}","page":"Home","text":"simulationFailed(simulation::Simulation, monad_id::Int)\nsimulationFailed(simulation_id::Int, monad_id::Int)\n\nMark a simulation as failed and remove it from its monad's constituent list.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.simulationFailed"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.simulationIDs-Tuple{GSASampling}","page":"Home","text":"simulationIDs(gsa_sampling::GSASampling)\n\nReturn the simulation IDs run in the sensitivity analysis.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.simulationIDs"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.simulationIDs-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"simulationIDs()\n\nReturn all simulation IDs in the database.  Overloaded forms accept a trial, sampling, monad, or simulation object.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.simulationIDs"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.simulationsTable-Tuple{AbstractArray{<:AbstractTrial}}","page":"Home","text":"simulationsTable(args...; kwargs...)\n\nReturn a DataFrame with simulation data. See simulationsTableFromQuery for keyword arguments.\n\nargs... can be:\n\nAny AbstractTrial objects (or arrays thereof)\nA vector of simulation IDs\nOmitted (returns data for all simulations)\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.simulationsTable"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.simulationsTableFromQuery-Tuple{String}","page":"Home","text":"simulationsTableFromQuery(query::String; remove_constants::Bool=true, sort_by=String[], sort_ignore=[:SimID; shortLocationVariationID.(projectLocations().varied)])\n\nReturn a DataFrame for the given SQL query on the simulations table.\n\nBy default, constant columns and raw ID columns are removed.\n\nArguments\n\nquery::String: The SQL query to execute.\n\nKeyword Arguments\n\nremove_constants::Bool: If true, removes columns that have the same value for all simulations. Defaults to true.\nsort_by::Vector{String}: A vector of column names to sort the table by. Defaults to all columns. To populate this argument, it is recommended to first print the table to see the column names.\nsort_ignore::Vector{String}: A vector of column names to ignore when sorting. Defaults to the simulation ID and the variation IDs associated with the simulations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.simulationsTableFromQuery"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.simulator-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"simulator()\n\nReturn the active AbstractSimulator backend.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.simulator"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.simulatorDir-Tuple{AbstractSimulator}","page":"Home","text":"simulatorDir(sim::AbstractSimulator)::String\n\nReturn the path to the simulator's root directory.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.simulatorDir"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.simulatorInfo-Tuple{AbstractSimulator}","page":"Home","text":"simulatorInfo(sim::AbstractSimulator)::String\n\nReturn a human-readable string describing the current simulator version.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.simulatorInfo"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.simulatorVersionIDName-Tuple{AbstractSimulator}","page":"Home","text":"simulatorVersionIDName(sim::AbstractSimulator)::String\n\nReturn the SQL column name used for the simulator version FK in the simulations, monads, and samplings tables (e.g. \"physicell_version_id\").\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.simulatorVersionIDName"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.simulatorVersionIDName-Tuple{}","page":"Home","text":"simulatorVersionIDName()\n\nReturn the SQL column name used for the simulator version FK. Delegates to simulatorVersionIDName(sim) on the active simulator.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.simulatorVersionIDName"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.simulatorVersionSchema-Tuple{AbstractSimulator}","page":"Home","text":"simulatorVersionSchema(sim::AbstractSimulator)::String\n\nReturn the SQL sub-schema (as a String) for the simulator version table. Used when initializing the database.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.simulatorVersionSchema"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.simulatorVersionTableName-Tuple{AbstractSimulator}","page":"Home","text":"simulatorVersionTableName(sim::AbstractSimulator)::String\n\nReturn the name of the simulator version table in the database (e.g. \"physicell_versions\").\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.simulatorVersionTableName"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.sqliteDataType-Tuple{ElementaryVariation}","page":"Home","text":"sqliteDataType(ev::ElementaryVariation)\nsqliteDataType(data_type::DataType)\n\nMap a Julia data type to its SQLite column type string.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.sqliteDataType"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.statusCodeID-Tuple{String}","page":"Home","text":"statusCodeID(status_code::String)\n\nReturn the database ID for status_code.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.statusCodeID"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.stmtToDataFrame-Tuple{SQLite.Stmt, Any}","page":"Home","text":"stmtToDataFrame(stmt_str, params; db::SQLite.DB=centralDB(), is_row::Bool=false)\nstmtToDataFrame(stmt::SQLite.Stmt, params; is_row::Bool=false)\n\nExecute a prepared statement with params and return the result as a DataFrame.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.stmtToDataFrame"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.tableColumns-Tuple{String}","page":"Home","text":"tableColumns(table_name::String; db::SQLite.DB=centralDB())\n\nReturn the column names of table_name in db.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.tableColumns"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.tableExists-Tuple{String}","page":"Home","text":"tableExists(table_name::String; db::SQLite.DB=centralDB())\n\nReturn true if table_name exists in db.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.tableExists"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.tableIDName-Tuple{String}","page":"Home","text":"tableIDName(table::String; strip_s::Bool=true)\n\nReturn the ID column name for table (e.g. \"config_id\" for \"configs\").\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.tableIDName"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.trialFolder-Tuple{Type{<:AbstractTrial}, Int64}","page":"Home","text":"trialFolder(T::Type{<:AbstractTrial}, id::Int)\ntrialFolder(T::AbstractTrial)\n\nReturn the output folder path for trial type T with the given ID.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.trialFolder"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.updateDatabaseOnCompletion-Tuple{Int64, Int64, Bool}","page":"Home","text":"updateDatabaseOnCompletion(simulation_id::Int, monad_id::Int, success::Bool)\n\nUpdate the simulation status in the database after it finishes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.updateDatabaseOnCompletion"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.upgradeMilestones-Tuple{AbstractSimulator}","page":"Home","text":"upgradeMilestones(sim::AbstractSimulator)::Vector{VersionNumber}\n\nReturn a sorted vector of milestone VersionNumbers that have associated database schema changes. upgradeToMilestone is called for each milestone between the current database version and the target package version.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.upgradeMilestones"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.upgradePackage-Tuple{AbstractSimulator, SQLite.DB, VersionNumber, VersionNumber, Bool}","page":"Home","text":"upgradePackage(sim::AbstractSimulator, db::SQLite.DB, from_version::VersionNumber, to_version::VersionNumber, auto_upgrade::Bool)\n\nDrive the database migration from from_version to to_version for the simulator framework sim.\n\nFor each milestone v in upgradeMilestones(sim) with from_version < v ≤ to_version, calls upgradeToMilestone(sim, v, auto_upgrade). After a successful milestone upgrade the version table is updated immediately so that a partial upgrade is recoverable. If any milestone fails the chain is aborted and false is returned.\n\nAfter all milestones pass, if to_version is beyond the last milestone the version table is stamped with to_version (a \"no schema change\" bump).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.upgradePackage"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.upgradeToMilestone-Tuple{AbstractSimulator, Vararg{Any}}","page":"Home","text":"upgradeToMilestone(sim::AbstractSimulator, version::VersionNumber, auto_upgrade::Bool)::Bool\n\nApply the database schema migration required to bring the project database up to version. Called by upgradePackage for each milestone that needs to be crossed. Return true on success, false to abort the upgrade chain.\n\nImplementations are responsible for:\n\nPrompting the user (when auto_upgrade is false) for any large/destructive migrations.\nMaking all necessary DDL/DML changes to the database.\nNot updating the version table — upgradePackage does that after a successful return.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.upgradeToMilestone"},{"category":"function","location":"#ModelManager.useHPC","page":"Home","text":"useHPC([use::Bool=true])\n\nSet the global run_on_hpc flag to use.\n\nExamples\n\nuseHPC()        # enable sbatch wrapping\nuseHPC(true)    # same\nuseHPC(false)   # run simulations locally\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.useHPC"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.variationDataType-Union{Tuple{DiscreteVariation{T}}, Tuple{T}} where T","page":"Home","text":"variationDataType(ev::ElementaryVariation)\n\nGet the data type of the variation values.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.variationDataType"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.variationIDs-Tuple{Symbol, AbstractMonad}","page":"Home","text":"variationIDs(location::Symbol, M::AbstractMonad)\nvariationIDs(location::Symbol, sampling::Sampling)\n\nReturn the variation IDs for location associated with M or sampling.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.variationIDs"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.variationLocation-Tuple{ElementaryVariation}","page":"Home","text":"variationLocation(av::AbstractVariation)\n\nGet the location of a variation as a Symbol.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.variationLocation"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.variationTarget-Tuple{ElementaryVariation}","page":"Home","text":"variationTarget(av::AbstractVariation)\n\nGet the XMLPath target(s) of a variation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.variationTarget"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.variationValues-Tuple{DiscreteVariation}","page":"Home","text":"variationValues(ev::ElementaryVariation[, cdf])\n\nGet the values of an ElementaryVariation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.variationValues"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.variationValues-Tuple{Function, Vararg{Any}}","page":"Home","text":"variationValues(f::Function, ev::ElementaryVariation[, cdf])\n\nApply a function f to each of the variation values.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.variationValues"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.variationValues-Tuple{LatentVariation{<:Vector{<:Real}}}","page":"Home","text":"variationValues(lv::LatentVariation)\n\nCompute the variation values for all combinations of discrete latent parameters.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.variationValues"},{"category":"method","location":"#ModelManager.variationsToMonads-Tuple{InputFolders, AbstractArray{VariationID}}","page":"Home","text":"variationsToMonads(inputs, variation_ids)\n\nReturn an array of Monads matching the shape of variation_ids.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"ModelManager.variationsToMonads"}]
}
